265
00:18:08,880 --> 00:18:12,240
 This means our lives are not accidents to God.

266
00:18:12,240 --> 00:18:17,480
 (speaking in foreign language)

267
00:18:17,480 --> 00:18:34,560
 - So God's seeing of us precede our shame

268
00:18:34,560 --> 00:18:36,240
 or even our existence.

269
00:18:36,240 --> 00:18:39,320
 And that's why David, the poet, can say,

270
00:18:39,320 --> 00:18:43,720
 I praise you because I am fearfully and wonderfully made.

271
00:18:43,720 --> 00:18:48,720
 God seeing you gives life rather than death.

272
00:18:48,720 --> 00:18:53,800
 (speaking in foreign language)

273
00:18:53,800 --> 00:19:04,080
 - And here at the end,

274
00:19:04,080 --> 00:19:07,160
 the psalm turns personal and prayerful.

275
00:19:07,160 --> 00:19:11,640
 It says verses 23 and 24.

276
00:19:11,640 --> 00:19:15,400
 Search me, O God, and know my heart,

277
00:19:15,400 --> 00:19:18,640
 and test me, and know my anxious thoughts.

278
00:19:18,640 --> 00:19:21,600
 See if there's any offensive way in me

279
00:19:21,600 --> 00:19:25,160
 and lead me in the way everlasting.

280
00:19:25,160 --> 00:19:29,160
 (speaking in foreign language)

281
00:19:35,080 --> 00:19:37,800
 - And this is, I think, the most beloved line

282
00:19:37,800 --> 00:19:39,000
 in the entire psalm,

283
00:19:39,000 --> 00:19:42,280
 or the most surprising line in the psalm.

284
00:19:42,280 --> 00:19:46,120
 And the psalm invites us to follow God and to trust Him.

285
00:19:46,120 --> 00:19:51,120
 And it does not ask God to look away from us,

286
00:19:51,120 --> 00:19:54,880
 ask God to look even deeper in our lives.

287
00:19:54,880 --> 00:19:58,800
 (speaking in foreign language)

288
00:20:04,920 --> 00:20:07,400
 - And psalm 139, let me conclude,

289
00:20:07,400 --> 00:20:10,880
 calls you, or all of us, to know God.

290
00:20:10,880 --> 00:20:13,880
 And it's not just knowing about Him, to know Him.

291
00:20:13,880 --> 00:20:17,000
 And to be known by God is actually grace,

292
00:20:17,000 --> 00:20:18,480
 and to grow in Him.

293
00:20:18,480 --> 00:20:23,480
 (speaking in foreign language)

294
00:20:35,080 --> 00:20:39,000
 (speaking in foreign language)

295
00:20:39,000 --> 00:20:44,880
 - And knowing God here means we stop hiding from Him.

296
00:20:44,880 --> 00:20:47,760
 We can be honest and we can be open

297
00:20:47,760 --> 00:20:49,520
 and transparent before God.

298
00:20:49,520 --> 00:20:52,960
 And it means we allow God not only to comfort us,

299
00:20:52,960 --> 00:20:54,400
 but to lead us.

300
00:20:54,400 --> 00:20:57,560
 And the gaze of God, the sight of Him,

301
00:20:57,560 --> 00:21:00,720
 does not merely reveal who we really are,

302
00:21:00,720 --> 00:21:05,720
 but lead us into ways of everlasting life following Him.

303
00:21:05,720 --> 00:21:10,080
 (speaking in foreign language)

304
00:21:10,080 --> 00:21:25,560
 - And today, I wanna invite you to conclude with a prayer,

305
00:21:25,560 --> 00:21:29,640
 to come before this God, and to accept Him,

306
00:21:29,640 --> 00:21:32,880
 and to love Him back, to relate to Him.

307
00:21:32,880 --> 00:21:37,280
 So let us all pray together.

308
00:21:37,280 --> 00:21:41,200
 Let's pray.

309
00:21:41,200 --> 00:21:43,000
 (speaking in foreign language)

310
00:21:43,000 --> 00:21:47,800
 - Lord, you see us completely, and you still love us.

311
00:21:47,800 --> 00:21:51,400
 (speaking in foreign language)

312
00:21:51,400 --> 00:21:56,400
 - Thank you, because your gaze is not meant to shame us,

313
00:21:57,160 --> 00:22:00,200
 but to guide us and to love us.

314
00:22:00,200 --> 00:22:04,120
 (speaking in foreign language)

315
00:22:04,120 --> 00:22:10,200
 - And help us, Lord, not only to rest in being known by you,

316
00:22:10,200 --> 00:22:13,120
 but to truly know you.

317
00:22:13,120 --> 00:22:18,080
 (speaking in foreign language)

318
00:22:18,080 --> 00:22:22,360
 - And with the psalm, we wanna conclude

319
00:22:22,360 --> 00:22:27,360
 with our heartful prayer, lead us, God, in the way everlasting.

320
00:22:27,360 --> 00:22:33,560
 (speaking in foreign language)

321
00:22:33,560 --> 00:22:34,720
 - In Christ, we pray.

322
00:22:34,720 --> 00:22:37,200
 - Amen. - Amen.

323
00:22:37,200 --> 00:22:44,840
 - Well, God bless you, and always be seen by God this week,

324
00:22:44,840 --> 00:22:47,560
 and knowing that God is always watching over you

325
00:22:47,560 --> 00:22:49,680
 and caring for you, all right?

326
00:22:49,680 --> 00:22:53,680
 (speaking in foreign language)

